Razgulay Poised for Biggest Drop in Two Weeks as Sugar Declines

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-05T09:40:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/razgulay-poised-for-biggest-drop-in-two-weeks-as-sugar-declines.html
OAO  Razgulay Group (GRAZ) , a Russian sugar
producer, headed for its worst drop in more than two weeks as
white sugar fell in  London .  Its stock slipped as much as 4.1 percent and last traded
1.6 percent lower at 36.97 rubles by 1:25 p.m. in Moscow, poised
for its biggest fall since Aug. 19.  White sugar for October delivery declined $2, or 0.3
percent, to $751.80 a metric ton in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran at 
 Jcorcoran13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
